{"title_page": "Meri Kahani (album)", "text_new": "{{copyvio-revdel|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120531000533/http://www.gibsonguitar.in/News-Lifestyle/Features/hi-in/Atif-Aslams-Top-10-Non-Film-Songs.aspx|start1=950848232|end1=950914212}}\n{{More citations needed|date=April 2020}}{{Infobox album\n| name         = Meri Kahani\n| type         = [[Studio Album]]\n| artist       = [[Atif Aslam]]\n| cover        =\n| alt          = \n| released     = 08 January 2008\n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Pop Music|Pop]], [[Rock Music|Rock]]\n| length       = 49:13\n| language     = [[Hindi]], [[Urdu]]\n| label        = [[Tips Industries|Tips Music]]\n| producer     = \n| prev_title   = [[Doorie]]\n| prev_year    = 2006\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n}}\n\nAfter the success of first two albums, [[Atif Aslam]] released his third solo album '''Meri Kahani''' in 2008.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hotfridaytalks.com/music/best-non-film-songs-from-atif-aslam/|title=Best Non-Film Songs From Atif Aslam|last=Nikam|first=Sohil|date=2018-07-15|website=HotFridayTalks|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iwmbuzz.com/music/snippets-music/atif-aslam-overrated-singer/2020/03/26|title=Is Atif Aslam an overrated singer?|last=Team|first=Author: Editorial|date=2020-03-26|website=IWMBuzz|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>\n\n== Performance ==\n'''\"Rabba Sacheya'''\" is synonymous with [[Faiz Ahmad Faiz]]'s poem. This song revolves around corruption in society and the struggle to keep a poor man alive. \"'''Meri Kahani'''\" song relates to lost memories, childhood and nostalgia. Piano is used in the song \"'''Mann Hota Hai'''\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120531000533/http://www.gibsonguitar.in/News-Lifestyle/Features/hi-in/Atif-Aslams-Top-10-Non-Film-Songs.aspx|title=Atif Aslam\u2019s Top 10 Non-Film Songs|date=2012-05-31|website=web.archive.org|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>\n\n== Track listing ==\n{| 